          "The entry-level job market you are entering is structurally different from the one your senior colleagues entered three years ago. Big-tech new-graduate hiring is down 55% since 2019. Thirty-seven percent of hiring managers say they prefer AI over junior hires for standard implementation tasks. The market for students who can only do the tasks AI does  write standard content, execute basic code, produce routine analysis  is shrinking. The market for students who can direct AI effectively, evaluate its outputs critically, and bring domain knowledge and contextual judgment to AI-assisted work is growing at 340% per year.",
